The paper deals with optimization problems related to sensor placement on a network, which is a classic problem in computer science. The use of planar graphs and the Four Color Theorem suggests that the paper may belong to the categories of Discrete Mathematics (cs.DM), Graph Theory (cs.GT), Computational Geometry (cs.CG), or Numerical Analysis (cs.NA). Additionally, the problem of finding optimal sensor placement involves algorithmic complexity, which is a topic typically studied in the category of Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS).
